name: Maya's Pizza
address: P2P3+72W, Jl. Pelapuan, Pelapuan, Kec. Busung Biu, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81152, Indonesia
review 1: Awesome place!   This place should have a 1000+ reviews.   I went here twice and will go again if I'm in the area.  Awesome view next to a stream!  The pizza was great!  Recommend!
review 2: 5 stars for all and I dont do this often but in this case all deserved. What a hidden gem, the food was great and what a location along the river, it is truly a hidden gem.
review 3: Fantastic place and lovely owner! Had a pizza which was very tasty with good cheese and tasty toppings and a good fresh strawberry juice. The restaurant is in the middle of a lush green sea of forestry and next to a flowing river making it a very relaxing atmosphere. Also had a very nice conversation with Maya who speaks English very well. The only thing that could have been better was the pizza dough which was quite thick and undercooked for my taste.
review 4: Tasty food, local prices, very welcoming owners and the surroundings are amazing too. Recommend!
review 5: Such a lovely little place with very kind people. Too bad it was dark when we arrived,  because the setting seemed to be very nice next to the river. The pizza was also good n tasty. Medium size was the perfect portion for a light meal. We were warned it might be spicy, but for us it wasn't that bad. We were offered some local fruits and dessert to taste as well, so kind! Also the price is hard to beat, so would definitely recommend!
